To keep things organized and have a clear structure;
Easier to edit or test code;
When working on a large project, only need to consider what it's relevant rathen than all the codes;
Codes can be reusable;
Help with "Encapsulation" - Encapsulation in Java is a mechanism of wrapping the data (variables) and code acting on the 
data (methods) together as a single unit. In encapsulation, the variables of a class will be hidden from other classes, 
and can be accessed only through the methods of their current class. Therefore, it is also known as data hiding.
